==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spadiceous
<hw>Spa*di"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>spadix</ets>, <ets>-icis</ets>, a date-brown or nut-brown color.
See <er>Spadix</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of a bright clear brown or
chestnut color.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Bearing flowers on a spadix; of
the nature of a spadix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spadicose</ent>⟦br⟧
